@Repository
public class UserDaoImpl implements UserDao {
  private final JdbcTemplate jdbcTemplate;

  public UserDaoImpl(DataSource dataSource) {
    this.jdbcTemplate = new JdbcTemplate(dataSource);
  }

  @Override
  public void updateMultipleRecords(List<User> data) {
    String sql = "UPDATE users SET column1 = ?, column2 = ?, ... WHERE id = ?";
    for (User user : data) {
      jdbcTemplate.update(sql, user.getColumn1(), user.getColumn2(), ..., user.getId());
    }
  }
}
```

In this example:
- `JdbcTemplate` is used from the Spring JDBC module to perform database operations.
- The `DataSource` is injected into the `UserDaoImpl` constructor.
- `updateMultipleRecords` method performs the update operation using SQL statements with placeholders (`?`) and the `update` method of `JdbcTemplate`.
- Replace `column1`, `column2`, etc. with the actual column names from your "users" table, and adjust the placeholders and method arguments accordingly.

Remember to import the necessary classes and configure the data source in your project's configuration files.

